					<span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/kate-mctiriss" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1223059); return false;"  ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=1223059&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610224492" alt="Kate McTiriss" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=1223059)"/></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/kate-mctiriss" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1223059); return false;" >Kate McTiriss</a></span> <span class="odate time_1410887397 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">16 Sep 2014 17:09</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-2111103">
									

<p>Howdy, Kate here. Consider me a candidate.</p>
<p>I posted <a href="/scp-072">my first article</a> back in October 2011, and have been an active reader since, beginning to write again recently. I'm highly active in chat, providing constructive feedback to new posters.</p>
<p>I've got extensive online community direction experience: I moderate the 90,500-subscriber <a href="http://reddit.com/r/smashbros">/r/smashbros</a>, which has been one of the fastest-growing communities on Reddit this year. In addition, I formerly managed unofficial Twitter feeds for two webcomics with a combined 19,000 followers. In the real world, I've been marketing director of a startup making $1 million/yr in revenue, where I managed their online communications and <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=O-SOfPYqKPM&amp;list=UUZUThWiFMv_uYZKY59CmboA">wrote a national TV commercial</a>. I currently manage political campaigns as a community organizer. I've also done graphic design, video editing and audio mixing, which can best be seen on my <a href="/dixieland-nightmare-magic-hub">recent Tale hub</a>.</p>
<p>On staff, I'd look to:</p>
<ol>
<li><strong>Encourage new users</strong> and provide them with resources and feedback they need to grow their skills. We lose a lot of interested writers with good ideas to a sense of malaise or frustration due to their initial execution being subpar.</li>
<li><strong>Grow the Foundation's real-world presence</strong>. I'd propose starting an email list highlighting monthly featured articles and increase the activity and reach of official social media outposts for the Foundation.</li>
<li>Work to <strong>better square our copyright status</strong>, indicating sources and disclaimers for popular articles with non-Creative Commons imagery.</li>
</ol>
<p>I appreciate the consideration. The SCP Foundation is a high-quality tentpole of modern Internet fiction, and it's due to the strength of its leadership. I look forward to contributing to its future growth and success.</p>

