			<div class="content" id="post-content-2111170">
									

<p>I'd like to believe that I'd make a good staff member.</p>
<p>I've been contributing to the site for several years now, in a wide variety of formats. I'm generally fairly active on both the forums and the chat, where I try my best to provide brainstorming help and critiques to anyone who asks. I'd like to think that I'm pretty well known among Site members, and I really, desperately hope that I've earned a good reputation. I always seek to promote a culture of professional and active help with the literary content of the site, especially fostering and encouraging new members, and I am pathologically allergic to drama in all forms.</p>
<p>I have significant experience in a wide variety of archival research. I also possess a technical grounding in the history of science and technology, in addition to significant experience in professional-level creative writing critiquing.</p>
<p>Pretty much everyone else who has posted in this thread is also an excellent choice for Staff, but I'd be honoured if I was accepted.</p>

